verbs.description: strapple (third-person singular simple present strapples, present participle strappling, simple past and past participle strappled)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To bind with a strap; strap; entangle.
examples: Sansen-tsuki is thrown from the full-frontal hachiji-dachi position, fists inverted and on the waist, knees bent and legs spread as if you were trying to strapple railroad tracks.
